\cos(\phi-\epsilon)=\cos\,\phi-(\mu\cos\,\phi-\nu\sin\,\phi)
\sin(\phi-\epsilon)=\sin\,\phi-(\mu\sin\,\phi+\nu\cos\,\phi)
\mu=2\sin^2\frac{\epsilon}{2}
\nu=\sin\,\epsilon
1^\circ
\mu=2\sin^2\frac{\pi}{360}\approx 1.523048436087608\times10^{-4}
\nu=\sin\frac{\pi}{180}\approx 1.745240643728351\times 10^{-2}
